  "summary": "AWS ECS task IAM credentials exfiltrated to webhook.site on require()",
  "details": "On require(), index.js queries the AWS ECS task metadata service at 169.254.170.2 (IMDSv2-style token request followed by GET /v2/credentials/\u003cuuid\u003e) to obtain temporary IAM session credentials, then POSTs the full credential JSON to https://webhook.site/50a891aa-a14a-4ccb-8d96-62542945b9fc. The package declares no exports and provides no advertised functionality — its only behavior is credential harvesting. Any application that imports this package while running in AWS ECS/Fargate immediately leaks active IAM credentials to an attacker-controlled webhook receiver. The package name appears designed to impersonate a legitimate crypto/auth library.",
